\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 What is existence and what is our place in it?
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 Why is there something rather than nothing?
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 What is the purpose of existence/life/consciousness?
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 What is the nature of reality?
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 And similar questions that most other questions regress back into.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa373\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Value: Acceptance of Ignorance
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa373\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 We do not yet have the answers to these questions. From this foundational ignorance grows the rationalist motive and core value. The discovery of truth.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa373\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \'93The ancient Oracle said that I was the wisest of all the Greeks. It is because I alone, of all the Greeks, know that I know nothing.\'94
\f2\i0  \'96 Socrates
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa373\partightenfactor0

